  <Subject Subject_ID="300015001">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300014908</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>coating by composition or origin [300014908], coating (material) [300014907], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a finish applied to bronze by using heat and a combination of copper nitrate, ammonium chloride, iron nitrate, or other chemicals. Depending upon the combination of chemicals used, the effects are dark brown, blackish, greenish, bluish, or reddish.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a una terminación aplicada al bronce utilizando calor y una combinación de nitrato de cobre, cloruro de amonio, nitrato de hierro y otros productos químicos. Según la combinación de los productos químicos utilizados, los efectos obtenidos son de color marrón oscuro, negruzco, verduzco, azulado o rojizo.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een afwerkingslaag die is aangebracht op brons door verhitting en een combinatie van kopernitraat, ammoniumchloride, ijzernitraat of andere chemicaliën. Afhankelijk van de gebruikte combinatie van chemicaliën is de resulterende kleur donkerbruin, zwartachtig, groenachtig, blauwachtig of roodachtig.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指運用熱氣和銅硝酸鹽、氯化銨、鐵硝酸鹽或其他化學材料的化合物，來塗在銅器上的末道漆。依據其所使用的化學材料組合，漆上去的效果會呈暗棕色、黑色、微綠、帶藍色，或者帶紅色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
